name: Baked Jalapeno Chicken and Cheese Wontons
author: Lela
summary: A healthier take on fried wontons, these spicy baked wontons are filled with chicken, jalapeno cream cheese, and Borden® Cheddar and Monterey Jack Cheese Shreds.
ingredients: ½ cup Borden® Cheddar and Monterey Jack Shreds
½ cup jalapeno-flavored cream cheese, softened
directions: Preheat oven to 425 degrees F (220 degrees C)
Line a rimmed baking sheet with parchment paper
Place cooked chicken cubes in a food processor
Add shredded Cheddar and Monterey Jack cheese and jalapeno cream cheese
If mixture appears dry, add more cream cheese, 1 tablespoon at a time
Place a heaping teaspoon of chicken-cheese mixture on the bottom corner of a wonton wrapper
Leave a 1/2 inch border around wonton
Brush the edges with water and fold over opposite corner to form a triangle
Place wontons on prepared baking sheet
Turn; lightly spray other side of wontons with cooking spray
Bake in preheated oven until the edges turn brown, 8 or 9 minutes
Serve warm with salsa or soy sauce
